{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17487541","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17487541"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T03:14:04+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T03:14:04+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"385"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"385","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/385"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.21,0.04,0.25,0.32,0.18]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"385"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"108874"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"385","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/385"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"385"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"91239"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"5"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"66"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"78"},{"type":"tags","id":"1151"},{"type":"tags","id":"3376"},{"type":"tags","id":"4491"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"1088"},{"type":"contributions","id":"17225"},{"type":"contributions","id":"17241"},{"type":"contributions","id":"39424"},{"type":"contributions","id":"39665"},{"type":"contributions","id":"40517"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"108874","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/108874"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 52-year-old man presents for a follow up endoscopy after a recent episode of gastrointestinal bleeding due to severe reflux oesophagitis. He was commenced on high-dose esomeprazole and his reflux symptoms are now well controlled. He smoked 10 cigarettes a day until quitting recently. He drinks two beers daily. He has no other significant medical history and takes no other regular medications.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOn examination, he appears well with vital signs within normal limits. His body mass index is 31 kg/m2. A repeat endoscopy shows healed oesophagitis with a 4 cm circumferential column of salmon-coloured mucosa. 4-quadrant biopsies confirm intestinal metaplasia with areas of low-grade dysplasia.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following management options is the most appropriate?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Lifestyle modification","Fundoplication","Repeat endoscopy in 2-3 years","Radiofrequency ablation","Endoscopic mucosal resection"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":[],"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient has been diagnosed with Barrett\u0027s oesophagus with low-grade dysplasia, which requires careful consideration due to the increased risk of progression to oesophageal adenocarcinoma. In this setting, either close endoscopic surveillance or endoscopic eradication would be recommended depending on patient preferences. Of the available options, \u003Cstrong\u003Eradiofrequency ablation\u003C/strong\u003E is the most appropriate. This involves controlled thermal ablation of the Barrett\u0027s mucosa, allowing regeneration with normal squamous epithelium.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe management approach to Barrett\u0027s oesophagus is influenced by patient factors and disease factors including the presence of dysplasia or visible mucosal irregularities. While there is some variation between guidelines, general recommendations are as follows:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ENon-dysplastic Barrett\u0027s: \u003C/strong\u003Eendoscopic surveillance every 2-5 years depending on the length of the Barrett\u0027s segment and the guideline\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIndefinite for dysplasia: \u003C/strong\u003Eoptimise medical reflux therapy and repeat endoscopy within 6 months\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELow-grade dysplasia: \u003C/strong\u003Eeither endoscopic eradication therapy or 6-monthly surveillance\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHigh-grade dysplasia and early intramucosal adenocarcinoma:\u003C/strong\u003E endoscopic eradication therapy, which may involve a combination of:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAblative therapy\u003C/strong\u003E (i.e. radiofrequency ablation) if no mucosal abnormalities are present\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EEndoscopic resection\u003C/strong\u003E (i.e. endoscopic mucosal resection or endoscopic submucosal dissection) of mucosal irregularities - this is both therapeutic and enables histological assessment of the resected specimen\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIf there is evidence of adenocarcinoma invasion beyond the submucosa, staging investigations and referral to an oncology centre\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EVisible mucosal irregularities\u003C/strong\u003E should undergo endoscopic resection and histological examination (see high-grade dysplasia)\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAs such,\u003Cstrong\u003E surveillance endoscopy in 2-3 years\u003C/strong\u003E would be inappropriate for Barrett\u0027s oesophagus with low-grade dysplasia as it would risk missing progression to high-grade dysplasia or adenocarcinoma. If surveillance is preferred over eradication, a 6-month interval would be recommended. \u003Cstrong\u003EEndoscopic mucosal resection\u003C/strong\u003E is typically reserved for visible lesions or areas of high-grade dysplasia, rather than the diffuse low-grade dysplasia described in this case.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELifestyle modifications\u003C/strong\u003E such as weight loss and dietary changes are important adjunctive measures in reducing gastro-oesophageal reflux as part of Barrett\u0027s management. However, given that his symptoms are currently well-controlled and low-grade dysplasia has been found, lifestyle modification alone is not the best management approach.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFundoplication\u003C/strong\u003E is a surgical anti-reflux procedure that can be considered for patients with persistent reflux symptoms despite optimal medical and lifestyle management. However, it is not otherwise indicated for Barrett\u0027s oesophagus management. Such a procedure would increase the complexity of initial surveillance as part of the Barrett\u0027s would be within the wrap.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIn this case, as the patient\u0027s symptoms are well controlled, the proton-pump inhibitor (esomeprazole) would be reduced to once daily (40mg).\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Patients with Barrett\u0027s oesophagus and low-grade dysplasia are recommended to undergo close surveillance or endoscopic ablation.","The risk of progression to adenocarcinoma in Barrett\u0027s oesophagus increases with the presence of dysplasia."],"references":["Shaheen NJ, Falk GW, Iyer PG, et al. Diagnosis and Management of Barrett\u0027s Esophagus: An Updated ACG Guideline. Am J Gastroenterol. 2022;117(4):559-587. Available at: https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC10259184/","Weusten BLAM, Bisschops R, Dinis-Ribeiro M, et al. Diagnosis and management of Barrett esophagus: European Society of Gastrointestinal Endoscopy (ESGE) Guideline. Endoscopy. 2023;55(12):1124-1146. Available at: https://www.thieme-connect.com/products/ejournals/abstract/10.1055/a-2176-2440","Whiteman DC, Kendall BJ. Barrett\u0027s oesophagus: epidemiology, diagnosis and clinical management. Med J Aust. 2016;205(7):317-324. Available at: https://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/full/10.5694/mja16.00796","Barret M, Pioche M, Terris B, et al. Endoscopic radiofrequency ablation or surveillance in patients with Barrett\u2019s oesophagus with confirmed low-grade dysplasia: a multicentre randomised\u00a0trial. Gut 2021; 70:1014\u201322."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"91239"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"385"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"91239","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/91239"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-07-14T10:50:20+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-07-14T10:51:26+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"385"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"108874"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"5","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/5"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udd2d","name":"Gastroenterology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:43+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"25","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/25"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc68\u200d\ud83d\udc69\u200d\ud83d\udc66","name":"General Practice","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"6"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"66","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/66"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Management","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"72","links":{"se